## Design guardrails

- Keep implementation inside `libs/sdk-dsl`
- Keep runtime package boundary clean; `document-processor` is test-only
- Use only public imports from `@blue-labs/language` and `@blue-labs/document-processor`
- Do not import from internal `src/...` paths across libraries
- Do not redesign stage-1/stage-2 APIs unless needed to preserve compatibility
- Prefer thin helpers that build runtime-correct contracts/events already defined by the mapping reference

## Behavioral guardrails

- `myOsAdmin(...)` must materialize the standard admin contracts needed for admin-delivered events on non-admin document types
- The helper must not silently force the root document `type`
- triggered-event matcher helpers must bind to the correct triggered-event channel and set matchers deterministically
- MyOS step helpers should be convenience wrappers over the same runtime-correct event shapes the processor expects
- Do not assume a repo-native `Common/Named Event`
- Do not widen scope to access/agency/AI/payments during this stage

